[ MUSIC ]

03:30.578 --> 03:45.593
[ MUSIC ]

04:02.843 --> 04:04.812
[ SNARLING ]

04:05.879 --> 04:20.661
[ ROCK MUSIC ]

04:35.543 --> 04:50.524
[ ROCK MUSIC ]

05:05.573 --> 05:20.588
[ ROCK MUSIC ]

05:35.769 --> 05:39.407
[ ROCK MUSIC ]

05:39.407 --> 05:42.643
>> JESUS CHRIST, WHAT A DUMP.

05:42.643 --> 05:45.078
AND IN THE MIDDLE OF NOWHERE.

05:45.078 --> 05:47.781
>> YOU KNOW, IT'S BEEN TOO LONG.

05:47.781 --> 05:49.650
I'VE MISSED THIS PLACE.

05:49.650 --> 05:51.184
GOOD BURGERS.

05:51.184 --> 05:52.119
>> UGH.

05:52.119 --> 05:53.554
>> HEY, IT HAS CHARACTER.

05:53.554 --> 05:54.822
I LIKE IT.

05:54.822 --> 05:56.256
>> YOU WOULD.

05:56.256 --> 05:56.890
>> YOU'RE TOO SPOILED

05:56.890 --> 05:58.726
BY CITY LIFE, JAN.

05:58.726 --> 06:00.694
>> IT'S JANELLE.

06:00.694 --> 06:03.697
>> JAN, JANELLE, WHATEVER.

06:03.697 --> 06:04.231
>> YOU WANTED TO

06:04.231 --> 06:06.333
BRING HER ALONG.

06:06.333 --> 06:08.268
>> SO, YOUR FRIEND,

06:08.268 --> 06:09.770
OR COUSIN, WORKS HERE?

06:09.770 --> 06:11.138
>> YEAH.

06:11.138 --> 06:12.806
>> AND THIS GUY, RALPH,

06:12.806 --> 06:14.007
HE KNOWS WHERE WE'RE GOING?

06:14.007 --> 06:15.476
YOU'VE BEEN THERE BEFORE, RIGHT?

06:15.476 --> 06:16.043
>> YES.

06:16.043 --> 06:16.577
>> SHIT, ARE YOU WRITING

06:16.577 --> 06:17.778
A BOOK ON THIS TRIP?

06:17.778 --> 06:18.846
>> HEY, MAYBE.

06:18.846 --> 06:19.713
WHAT, ARE YOU AFRAID THE WORLD'S

06:19.713 --> 06:21.114
GONNA FIND OUT ABOUT YOU?

06:21.114 --> 06:21.882
>> WHAT?

06:21.882 --> 06:22.450
[ CHUCKLING ]

06:22.450 --> 06:23.451
NO.

06:23.451 --> 06:25.185
YOU'RE SO FUCKING ANNOYING.

06:25.185 --> 06:26.454
>> RUNS IN THE FAMILY.

06:26.454 --> 06:28.288
LET'S GO.

06:28.288 --> 06:29.923
[ CHUCKLING ]

06:31.659 --> 06:32.760
>> MY MOM AND HER MOM

06:32.760 --> 06:33.561
THOUGHT IT'D BE A GOOD IDEA

06:33.561 --> 06:34.662
TO BRING HER.

06:34.662 --> 06:35.696
LIKE SHE MIGHT

06:35.696 --> 06:38.065
LOOSEN UP OR SOMETHING.

06:38.065 --> 06:39.066
>> I DUNNO.

06:39.066 --> 06:40.300
IT'S A PRETTY LONG STICK

06:40.300 --> 06:41.268
UP HER ASS.

06:41.268 --> 06:42.903
[ LAUGHING ]

06:42.903 --> 06:45.939
>> EXCUSE ME, YOUNG 'UNS?

06:45.939 --> 06:47.541
YOU KIDS,

06:47.541 --> 06:49.977
YOU AIN'T FROM AROUND HERE!

06:49.977 --> 06:52.012
>> WHAT GAVE IT AWAY?

06:52.012 --> 06:54.381
>> GOIN' UP IN THE HILLS?

06:54.381 --> 06:55.716
CAMPIN' ARE YA?

06:55.716 --> 06:56.650
>> YES, SIR.

06:56.650 --> 06:59.252
IT'S BEEN A WHILE, BUT, UM--

06:59.252 --> 07:00.020
I THINK WE'RE GONNA

07:00.020 --> 07:00.954
HAVE A GOOD TIME.

07:00.954 --> 07:02.389
>> BOOZE AND ROCK N' ROLL,

07:02.389 --> 07:03.491
I EXPECT!

07:03.491 --> 07:03.957
>> IT'S JUST GONNA BE

07:03.957 --> 07:05.759
SOME HARMLESS FUN, MISTER.

07:05.759 --> 07:07.227
>> HARMLESS?

07:07.227 --> 07:08.729
HA!

07:08.729 --> 07:12.533
OKAY, YOU KIDS GO HAVE SOME FUN.

07:12.533 --> 07:15.335
WHY, I REMEMBER SOME

07:15.335 --> 07:17.370
ADVENTURES UP THERE.

07:17.370 --> 07:19.106
[ CHUCKLING ]

07:19.106 --> 07:21.875
HAD MYSELF SOME LADIES UP THERE,

07:21.875 --> 07:24.244
IF'N YA KNOW WHAT I MEAN.

07:26.146 --> 07:27.314
TO BE YOUNG AGAIN!

07:27.314 --> 07:29.917
HA HA!

07:29.917 --> 07:31.051
>> AH...

07:31.051 --> 07:32.520
THAT'S A CRAZY OLD COOT.

07:32.520 --> 07:33.253
[ LAUGHING ]

07:33.253 --> 07:35.088
>> SURE IS.

07:38.158 --> 07:38.959
>> RALPH!

07:38.959 --> 07:39.693
>> HEY MAN, COOL!

07:39.693 --> 07:40.561
YOU'RE HERE.

07:40.561 --> 07:42.162
>> HEY, IT'S BEEN A WHILE.

07:42.162 --> 07:43.263
>> SURE HAS, MAN.

07:43.263 --> 07:44.431
WOW, FAR OUT.

07:44.431 --> 07:45.833
>> YEAH, HEY, UH-- YOU REMEMBER,

07:45.833 --> 07:46.900
UH, JANELLE AND CLAIRE?

07:46.900 --> 07:48.035
>> YEAH, YEAH.

07:48.035 --> 07:48.536
>> AND THIS IS

07:48.536 --> 07:49.770
MY COUSIN JOSEPHINE

07:49.770 --> 07:52.372
I WAS TELLING YOU ABOUT.

07:52.372 --> 07:54.041
>> UH...

07:54.041 --> 07:55.175
HI, I'M RALPH.

07:55.175 --> 07:56.544
>> JUST JO IS FINE.

07:56.544 --> 07:57.711
>> OH, UH...

07:57.711 --> 07:59.446
HI, JO.

07:59.446 --> 08:03.283
LET ME SHOW YOU THE PLACE.

08:03.283 --> 08:04.317
>> OKAY.

08:04.317 --> 08:05.686
>> ALL RIGHT.

08:05.686 --> 08:08.288
[ FAINT ROCK MUSIC PLAYING ]

08:13.661 --> 08:15.262
>> NOT THIS TIME.

08:15.262 --> 08:16.930
>> THAT'S UNFAIR!

08:16.930 --> 08:18.566
>> SHE'S MY COUSIN.

08:18.566 --> 08:20.868
>> AND I'M YOUR BEST FRIEND.

08:23.236 --> 08:24.404
>> RALPHIE, COULD YOU

08:24.404 --> 08:26.206
GET ME A BEER, PLEASE?

08:26.206 --> 08:29.176
>> SURE.

08:29.176 --> 08:31.579
[ GLASSES CLINKING ]

08:31.579 --> 08:32.580
>> OH MY GOSH.

08:32.580 --> 08:34.381
>> IT'S ON THE HOUSE.

08:34.381 --> 08:36.316
>> LIKE HELL IT IS, BOY!

08:36.316 --> 08:38.418
THAT'LL COME OUT OF YOUR CHECK.

08:38.418 --> 08:40.287
>> IT'S ON ME.

08:40.287 --> 08:43.056
>> AH, DON'T WORRY.

08:43.056 --> 08:45.025
IT'S ON THE HOUSE.

08:45.025 --> 08:46.159
YOU GUYS WANT ONE?

08:46.159 --> 08:48.228
>> YEAH.

08:48.228 --> 08:49.897
[ BOTTLE OPENING ]

08:49.897 --> 08:50.931
>> YOU GUYS OFF TO A WILD

08:50.931 --> 08:53.433
WEEKEND UP IN THE HILLS?

08:53.433 --> 08:54.301
>> YEAH, I WAS, UH--

08:54.301 --> 08:57.070
THINKIN' ABOUT NORTH LAKE.

08:57.070 --> 08:57.671
>> AND WHO DID I JUST

08:57.671 --> 08:59.740
BUY FREE BEERS FOR?

08:59.740 --> 09:00.908
>> JOSEPHINE.

09:00.908 --> 09:02.876
EVERYBODY CALLS ME JO.

09:02.876 --> 09:04.011
>> CHARMED.

09:04.011 --> 09:06.914
SHE'S GOT MANNERS, TOO.

09:06.914 --> 09:08.949
>> I GOTTA GO FINISH

09:08.949 --> 09:10.117
PUTTIN' AWAY THE ORDER.

09:10.117 --> 09:10.784
>> HEY, I REMEMBER THIS

09:10.784 --> 09:12.620
TROUBLEMAKER FROM YEARS AGO.

09:12.620 --> 09:13.420
>> YES, SIR.

09:13.420 --> 09:14.755
HEY, IT'S BEEN A WHILE.

09:14.755 --> 09:15.989
I'VE MISSED THIS PLACE.

09:15.989 --> 09:17.190
>> WE HAVEN'T GONE ANYWHERE.

09:17.190 --> 09:18.358
EVERY TIME YOU COME UP,

09:18.358 --> 09:18.959
WE'RE HERE.

09:18.959 --> 09:19.760
>> YEAH?

09:19.760 --> 09:20.460
>> I SUSPECT YOU FOLKS

09:20.460 --> 09:21.461
ARE HEADED OFF TO SAND LAKE

09:21.461 --> 09:23.430
TO DO SOME CAMPIN'.

09:23.430 --> 09:24.331
>> NO, ACTUALLY THEY WANNA

09:24.331 --> 09:26.433
GO OVER TO THE OLD ORCHARDS,

09:26.433 --> 09:28.769
BY HARPER LAKE.

09:28.769 --> 09:29.637
>> YOU DON'T GET YOUR SHIT DONE,

09:29.637 --> 09:31.538
BOY, YOU'RE NOT GOIN' ANYWHERE.

09:31.538 --> 09:32.673
>> AW, SIR, YOU WOULDN'T TAKE

09:32.673 --> 09:34.307
OUR GUIDE AWAY, WOULD YOU?

09:34.307 --> 09:35.809
>> CALL ME DOC, DARLIN'.

09:35.809 --> 09:37.444
AND NO, I WOULDN'T.

09:37.444 --> 09:37.911
BUT...

09:37.911 --> 09:39.479
HARPER LAKE, HUH?

09:39.479 --> 09:41.548
>> IS IT NOT A GOOD SPOT,

09:41.548 --> 09:43.651
DOC, SIR?

09:43.651 --> 09:44.451
>> IF YOU'RE GOIN',

09:44.451 --> 09:46.820
YOU OUGHTA KNOW.

09:46.820 --> 09:48.388
>> KNOW WHAT?

09:48.388 --> 09:50.791
>> THEM ORCHARDS AND LAKE,

09:50.791 --> 09:53.226
THAT WHOLE PATCH IS HAUNTED.

09:53.226 --> 09:55.128
[ LAUGHING ]

09:55.128 --> 09:56.664
>> OH, COME ON, YOU GUYS.

09:56.664 --> 09:58.265
HE'S JUST TRYING TO SCARE US.

09:58.265 --> 09:59.132
>> NO, NO, NO.

09:59.132 --> 10:00.668
LISTEN HERE...

10:00.668 --> 10:01.501
THERE'S AN EVIL

10:01.501 --> 10:02.569
IN THOSE REGIONS.

10:02.569 --> 10:05.706
WAKES UP EVERY 30 YEARS OR SO.

10:05.706 --> 10:06.907
>> AND LET ME GUESS,

10:06.907 --> 10:08.676
IT'S BEEN 30 YEARS?

10:08.676 --> 10:09.209
[ CHUCKLING ]

10:09.209 --> 10:10.343
>> OR... 15.

10:10.343 --> 10:12.646
>> FIVE, 15, 30...

10:12.646 --> 10:14.081
DOES IT MATTER?

10:14.081 --> 10:14.682
THIS IS THE YEAR

10:14.682 --> 10:16.016
IT WAKES UP, RIGHT?

10:16.016 --> 10:17.651
>> WELL, NO.

10:17.651 --> 10:18.551
>> SO, WHAT'S THE POINT

10:18.551 --> 10:19.820
OF WARNING US?

10:19.820 --> 10:21.054
>> I CAN'T HELP SPINNIN' TALES

10:21.054 --> 10:24.091
TO PRETTY YOUNG GALS LIKE YOU.

10:24.091 --> 10:25.392
>> OH, THAT MAKES IT

10:25.392 --> 10:26.960
SO MUCH BETTER.

10:26.960 --> 10:29.029
>> IT'S A COOL STORY...

10:32.099 --> 10:34.467
IF YOU WANNA HEAR IT.

10:36.203 --> 10:38.605
REALLY GOOD.

10:38.605 --> 10:41.008
REAL GOOD.

10:41.008 --> 10:42.710
CREEPY.

10:42.710 --> 10:45.913
>> FINE, I'LL BITE.

10:45.913 --> 10:47.815
TELL US THE STORY.

10:47.815 --> 10:49.182
>> IF YOU INSIST.

10:49.182 --> 10:50.417
>> I'D INSIST

10:50.417 --> 10:52.319
YOU LET RALPH LEAVE.

10:52.319 --> 10:55.255
>> WHAT'S THE STORY ABOUT?

10:55.255 --> 10:56.990
>> AN EVIL SCARECROW.

10:56.990 --> 10:58.025
[ ALL LAUGHING ]

10:58.025 --> 10:59.126
>> ARE YOU SERIOUS?

10:59.126 --> 11:00.560
>> AW, NO.

11:00.560 --> 11:02.930
ARE YOU, UH, TELLIN' THEM

11:02.930 --> 11:04.231
ABOUT THAT OLD THING AGAIN?

11:04.231 --> 11:05.833
I, UH...

11:05.833 --> 11:06.834
I DON'T KNOW.

11:06.834 --> 11:07.634
THAT, UH--

11:07.634 --> 11:09.737
THAT DOESN'T SEEM WISE.

11:09.737 --> 11:12.740
>> IT'S JUST A STORY, RIGHT?

11:12.740 --> 11:14.842
IT'S A GHOST STORY?

11:14.842 --> 11:17.610
>> WELL, YEAH, I GUESS.

11:19.646 --> 11:20.213
THEY'VE ALWAYS SAID

11:20.213 --> 11:22.382
THIS AREA'S BEEN CURSED.

11:22.382 --> 11:23.984
WEIRD ACCIDENTS,

11:23.984 --> 11:25.853
STRANGE THINGS HAPPENING.

11:25.853 --> 11:27.220
>> RALPH, YOU DON'T BELIEVE

11:27.220 --> 11:29.356
IT'S A SCARECROW, DO YOU?

11:29.356 --> 11:29.957
[ CHUCKLING ]

11:29.957 --> 11:31.024
>> 'COURSE HE DOESN'T.

11:31.024 --> 11:31.959
HE'S YOUNG AND DUMB,

11:31.959 --> 11:33.927
JUST LIKE ALL OF YOU ARE.

11:33.927 --> 11:34.661
IF YOU CAN'T SEE IT,

11:34.661 --> 11:35.796
OR TOUCH IT, OR SMELL IT,

11:35.796 --> 11:36.897
YOU DON'T BELIEVE IN IT.

11:36.897 --> 11:37.765
[ CHUCKLING ]

11:37.765 --> 11:38.331
WELL, LET ME TELL YOU

11:38.331 --> 11:39.299
ABOUT THE BEGINNING

11:39.299 --> 11:41.769
OF THE CURSE-- OR THE EVIL,

11:41.769 --> 11:43.103
IN THIS REGION.

11:43.103 --> 11:44.371
[ THUNDER RUMBLING ]

11:44.371 --> 11:45.238
IT ALL STARTED JUST

11:45.238 --> 11:45.939
BEFORE THE TURN

11:45.939 --> 11:47.640
OF THE LAST CENTURY.

11:47.640 --> 11:48.475
THEY SAY IT WAS A GROUP OF

11:48.475 --> 11:49.910
WITCHES AND WARLOCKS

11:49.910 --> 11:51.611
THAT STARTED IT ALL.

11:51.611 --> 11:52.679
OR THEY SAY IT WAS A GROUP

11:52.679 --> 11:54.047
OF ESCAPED MENTAL PATIENTS

11:54.047 --> 11:55.015
FROM THE OLD ASYLUM

11:55.015 --> 11:57.217
THE NEXT COUNTY OVER.

11:57.217 --> 11:59.419
>> OKAY, SO WAIT A MINUTE.

11:59.419 --> 12:00.320
WHICH IS IT?

12:00.320 --> 12:01.288
'CAUSE THAT'S, LIKE, TWO

12:01.288 --> 12:02.890
COMPLETELY DIFFERENT STORIES.

12:02.890 --> 12:03.523
>> I THOUGHT YOU

12:03.523 --> 12:04.992
WERE THE NICE ONE.

12:04.992 --> 12:06.126
>> I'M SORRY.

12:06.126 --> 12:07.460
>> AW, THAT'S OKAY.

12:07.460 --> 12:08.195
BUT IF YOU MUST KNOW,

12:08.195 --> 12:09.362
IT WAS BOTH.

12:09.362 --> 12:11.698
[ THUNDER RUMBLING ]

12:11.698 --> 12:12.465
LEGEND HAS IT,

12:12.465 --> 12:13.433
THERE WAS A FAMILY OF WITCHES

12:13.433 --> 12:14.501
AND WIZARDS THAT FOUNDED

12:14.501 --> 12:16.536
THIS HERE AREA AND TOWN.

12:16.536 --> 12:17.971
THEY KEPT TO THEMSELVES, MOSTLY,

12:17.971 --> 12:19.706
NOT HARMIN' NO ONE.

12:19.706 --> 12:21.809
ALTHOUGH, THERE WERE RUMORS,

12:21.809 --> 12:22.943
AND PEOPLE WERE AFRAID OF THEM,

12:22.943 --> 12:23.576
OF COURSE.

12:23.576 --> 12:24.711
>> OF COURSE.

12:24.711 --> 12:25.813
>> SHH!

12:25.813 --> 12:26.413
>> SORRY.

12:26.413 --> 12:29.016
>> SHH!!

12:29.016 --> 12:31.084
>> ANYWAY, LIKE I WAS SAYIN'...

12:31.084 --> 12:32.285
AFTER TIME, FOLKS GOT TO

12:32.285 --> 12:34.221
AVOIDING THEM FOR THE MOST PART.

12:34.221 --> 12:35.889
YOU SEE, THERE WAS A COUSIN,

12:35.889 --> 12:36.489
AND HE WEREN'T QUITE

12:36.489 --> 12:38.691
RIGHT IN THE HEAD.

12:38.691 --> 12:39.827
HE WOULD PRACTICE HIS

12:39.827 --> 12:41.962
INCANTATIONS OPENLY, SO PEOPLE

12:41.962 --> 12:45.198
COULD SEE, SCARIN' PEOPLE.

12:45.198 --> 12:46.299
ONE DAY, THOUGH, HE KIDNAPS

12:46.299 --> 12:47.400
HIMSELF ONE OF THE TOWNSFOLK'S

12:47.400 --> 12:49.736
KIDS, AND HE DOES SOMETHING

12:49.736 --> 12:51.271
TERRIBLE, AND TORTURES

12:51.271 --> 12:53.406
THE POOR KID, AND SACRIFICES HIM

12:53.406 --> 12:54.541
IN A DARK RITUAL.

12:54.541 --> 12:55.108
[ CHILD SCREAMING ]

12:55.108 --> 12:57.177
>> NO, NO!

12:57.177 --> 12:58.245
[ KNIFE STABBING ]

12:58.245 --> 12:59.112
>> WELL, THE TOWNSFOLKS

12:59.112 --> 13:00.380
GET ALL STIRRED UP,

13:00.380 --> 13:01.348
AND THEY GO TO THE FAMILY'S

13:01.348 --> 13:03.083
HOUSE AND STORM IT.

13:03.083 --> 13:04.384
THEY GRAB THE COUSIN

13:04.384 --> 13:05.652
AND TWO OTHER FAMILY MEMBERS,

13:05.652 --> 13:06.987
AND HAD A QUICK TRIAL.

13:06.987 --> 13:10.023
[ COLLECTIVE ANGRY CHATTER ]

13:10.023 --> 13:10.457
[ GAVEL CLACKING ]

13:10.457 --> 13:11.058
THEY FOUND THEM

13:11.058 --> 13:11.859
ALL GUILTY, AS THE COUSIN

13:11.859 --> 13:12.860
LAUGHED AND SPAT.

13:12.860 --> 13:14.661
[ EVIL LAUGHTER ]

13:14.661 --> 13:15.428
WELL, THE TOWNSFOLK

13:15.428 --> 13:16.329
HAD THEM ALL COMMITTED

13:16.329 --> 13:17.998
TO THE ASYLUM, WHERE, THROUGH

13:17.998 --> 13:19.432
TREATMENT, THEY WENT MAD.

13:19.432 --> 13:20.267
[ ELECTRICAL ZAPPING ]

13:20.267 --> 13:22.569
[ SCREAMING ]

13:22.569 --> 13:23.503
NOW, THE HEADS OF THE FAMILY

13:23.503 --> 13:24.737
GOT PLENTY ANGRY,

13:24.737 --> 13:25.672
AND THEY WENT TO THE ASYLUM

13:25.672 --> 13:26.639
AND KILLED EVERYONE THERE.

13:26.639 --> 13:28.408
PATIENTS, DOCTORS, ANYONE

13:28.408 --> 13:30.878
AND EVERYONE TO FREE THEIR KIN.

13:30.878 --> 13:31.979
THEY ESCAPED, AND MADE IT BACK

13:31.979 --> 13:34.414
TO THEIR HOMESTEAD.

13:34.414 --> 13:35.883
WHEN THE TOWNSFOLKS FOUND OUT,

13:35.883 --> 13:36.884
THEY BROKE INTO THE HOUSE

13:36.884 --> 13:37.550
AND DRUG THEM ALL OUT,

13:37.550 --> 13:38.618
AND HANGED THEM.

13:38.618 --> 13:40.387
[ COLLECTIVE ANGRY CHATTER ]

13:42.923 --> 13:45.492
[ THUNDER RUMBLING ]

13:45.492 --> 13:46.226
THEN, THEY BURNED

13:46.226 --> 13:47.327
THE HOUSE AND PROPERTY DOWN,

13:47.327 --> 13:48.161
AND SALTED THE EARTH

13:48.161 --> 13:48.896
TO MAKE SURE NOTHING

13:48.896 --> 13:52.900
HAPPENED THERE.

13:52.900 --> 13:53.901
THE FAMILY TOOK A LONG TIME TO

13:53.901 --> 13:55.768
DIE, THOUGH, WHILE SPOUTING OFF

13:55.768 --> 13:58.071
CURSES AND SPELLS.

13:58.071 --> 13:59.806
[ MYSTICAL INCANTATIONS ]

13:59.806 --> 14:00.573
WHEN THEY FINALLY DIED,

14:00.573 --> 14:01.474
THE TOWNSFOLK DIDN'T WANT

14:01.474 --> 14:02.809
TO BURN THE BODIES.

14:02.809 --> 14:03.776
SO THEY TOOK THEM DEEP

14:03.776 --> 14:04.912
INTO THE WOODS,

14:04.912 --> 14:06.179
SECRET-LIKE, 'CAUSE NOT

14:06.179 --> 14:08.015
ALL THE FAMILY WAS CAUGHT.

14:08.015 --> 14:08.916
THE TOWNSFOLK BELIEVED

14:08.916 --> 14:09.582
THAT THE FREE ONES COULD

14:09.582 --> 14:11.018
RESURRECT THE DEAD ONES,

14:11.018 --> 14:12.352
OR SOME SUCH NONSENSE.

14:12.352 --> 14:14.922
[ CHANTING ]

14:14.922 --> 14:15.755
SO A FEW OF THE BRAVE

14:15.755 --> 14:17.190
TOWNSMEN BURIED THE BODIES

14:17.190 --> 14:18.425
IN A SMALL CEMETERY THAT

14:18.425 --> 14:20.127
THEY HAD CREATED, HIDDEN AWAY

14:20.127 --> 14:23.030
SO NO ONE COULD FIND THEM.

14:23.030 --> 14:24.564
>> THIS IS ALL FASCINATING,

14:24.564 --> 14:26.199
BUT WHAT DOES IT HAVE TO DO

14:26.199 --> 14:27.034
WITH THE SCARECROW?

14:27.034 --> 14:27.667
>> PATIENCE, LAD.

14:27.667 --> 14:28.301
CHILL OUT.

14:28.301 --> 14:29.536
[ LAUGHTER ]

14:29.536 --> 14:30.470
NOW, WHERE WAS I?

14:30.470 --> 14:32.472
OH YES, THE SCARECROW.

14:32.472 --> 14:33.506
YOU SEE, THE TOWNSFOLK DIDN'T

14:33.506 --> 14:35.708
THINK TO WARD OFF THE CEMETERY,

14:35.708 --> 14:36.676
OR GET A WISE WOMAN

14:36.676 --> 14:38.578
OR WICCAN TO BLESS IT,

14:38.578 --> 14:40.580
SO THE DARK POWER SEEPED OUT.

14:40.580 --> 14:42.082
IT HAD FOUND, NOT TOO FAR AWAY--

14:42.082 --> 14:42.983
THERE WAS A CORNFIELD,

14:42.983 --> 14:44.817
LONG OVERGROWN, COMPLETE WITH

14:44.817 --> 14:46.786
AN ABANDONED SCARECROW.

14:46.786 --> 14:47.854
WELL, THOSE POWERS SEEPED INTO

14:47.854 --> 14:49.322
THAT THING, AND GAVE IT

14:49.322 --> 14:50.958
A HORRIBLE LIFE.

14:50.958 --> 14:51.992
SOME SAY IT AVENGES UPON

14:51.992 --> 14:53.360
THE DESCENDANTS OF THE TOWNSFOLK

14:53.360 --> 14:54.962
WHO HUNG THE FAMILY.

14:54.962 --> 14:55.963
SOME SAY IT SEARCHES FOR

14:55.963 --> 14:57.764
THE REMAINING FAMILY MEMBER.

14:57.764 --> 14:59.199
BUT IT LIVES AND EXISTS

14:59.199 --> 15:02.302
FOR PURELY EVIL PURPOSES.

15:02.302 --> 15:04.371
[ HISSING ]

15:06.339 --> 15:07.574
[ THUNDER CRACKLING ]

15:07.574 --> 15:08.575
>> SO DID THE ESCAPED FAMILY

15:08.575 --> 15:10.510
MEMBER EVER COME BACK?

15:10.510 --> 15:12.745
DID ANYTHING EVER HAPPEN?

15:12.745 --> 15:13.313
>> NO, NOTHING EVER

15:13.313 --> 15:14.982
REALLY HAPPENED.

15:14.982 --> 15:16.383
THEY SAY HE CHANGED HIS NAME,

15:16.383 --> 15:18.085
MOVED OUT OF TOWN.

15:18.085 --> 15:19.552
BEEN HIDDEN EVER SINCE.

15:19.552 --> 15:20.487
>> HE?

15:20.487 --> 15:22.589
>> OR SHE.

15:22.589 --> 15:25.425
>> SO, THAT REALLY HAPPENED?

15:27.427 --> 15:31.264
>> WELL, KIND OF, SORTA.

15:31.264 --> 15:32.499
>> WELL, WHY DIDN'T SOMEONE JUST

15:32.499 --> 15:34.067
GO DIG UP THE CEMETERY

15:34.067 --> 15:36.003
AND WARD IT, OR BIND IT

15:36.003 --> 15:37.537
LIKE YOU SAID?

15:37.537 --> 15:39.539
>> NO ONE KNOWS WHERE IT IS.

15:39.539 --> 15:40.407
>> YOU SAID IT ONLY COMES OUT

15:40.407 --> 15:42.342
EVERY 30 YEARS?

15:42.342 --> 15:43.576
>> 15.

15:43.576 --> 15:45.512
>> EVERY 15 YEARS?

15:45.512 --> 15:48.748
>> OOO, SCARY!

15:48.748 --> 15:49.382
[ CHUCKLING ]

15:49.382 --> 15:50.250
>> WELL, THE GRAVEYARD'S

15:50.250 --> 15:50.850
SUPPOSED TO BE AROUND

15:50.850 --> 15:51.918
THE HARPER LAKE AREA.

15:51.918 --> 15:53.520
SO THERE YOU GO.

15:53.520 --> 15:54.221
>> HASN'T ANYONE EVER

15:54.221 --> 15:55.888
GONE LOOKING FOR IT?

15:55.888 --> 15:57.424
>> WOULD YOU?

15:58.558 --> 15:59.759
ANYONE THAT HAS IS--

15:59.759 --> 16:01.028
>> THEY'VE ALL DISAPPEARED,

16:01.028 --> 16:01.861
RIGHT?

16:01.861 --> 16:03.730
[ LAUGHING ]

16:03.730 --> 16:04.897
>> WELL, SOME HAVE.

16:04.897 --> 16:06.033
SOME GET LOST AND NEVER FIND

16:06.033 --> 16:07.534
THEIR WAY BACK, AND SOME

16:07.534 --> 16:10.503
DON'T FIND ANYTHING AT ALL.

16:10.503 --> 16:11.171
>> DON'T WORRY.

16:11.171 --> 16:12.705
I'VE LIVED HERE MY WHOLE LIFE.

16:12.705 --> 16:15.042
NOTHING HAS HAPPENED.

16:15.042 --> 16:15.942
I MEAN, I'VE HEARD THE STORIES,

16:15.942 --> 16:17.377
BUT THAT'S ALL THEY ARE,

16:17.377 --> 16:19.279
STORIES TO SCARE KIDS.

16:19.279 --> 16:20.647
YOU DON'T GO TO SLEEP,

16:20.647 --> 16:21.881
THE SCARECROW'LL GET YA.

16:21.881 --> 16:22.549
STUFF LIKE THAT.

16:22.549 --> 16:23.716
[ CHUCKLING ]

16:23.716 --> 16:24.617
>> EAT YOUR VEGGIES

16:24.617 --> 16:26.353
OR THE SCARECROW'LL GET YA!

16:26.353 --> 16:27.254
[ SQUEALING AND LAUGHING ]

16:27.254 --> 16:27.787
>> AW, DON'T WORRY

16:27.787 --> 16:29.156
YOUR PRETTY LITTLE HEAD.

16:29.156 --> 16:29.656
YOU GOT RALPH TO

16:29.656 --> 16:32.859
TAKE CARE OF YA.

16:32.859 --> 16:34.494
IT'S JUST A STORY,

16:34.494 --> 16:36.096
IN EXCHANGE FOR FREE DRINKS.

16:36.096 --> 16:37.064
I DON'T GET TO SPEND MUCH TIME

16:37.064 --> 16:38.831
WITH PRETTY GIRLS LIKE YOU.

16:38.831 --> 16:39.832
>> YOU OLD CHARMER.

16:39.832 --> 16:40.600
>> MM-HMM.

16:40.600 --> 16:41.334
[ SCOFFING ]

16:41.334 --> 16:42.935
>> WE SHOULD GET GOING.

16:42.935 --> 16:44.071
>> WAIT, WAIT, WAIT,

16:44.071 --> 16:45.838
LET'S GET A PICTURE WITH DOC.

16:45.838 --> 16:46.973
>> SHIT.

16:46.973 --> 16:49.509
YOU ARE WRITING A BOOK.

16:49.509 --> 16:51.678
>> I JUST LIKE PICTURES.

16:53.413 --> 16:53.913
EXCUSE ME, WILL YOU

16:53.913 --> 16:56.083
TAKE THIS SHOT FOR US?

16:56.083 --> 16:57.884
>> UH, SURE.

16:57.884 --> 16:59.619
[ INDISTINCT CHATTER ]

16:59.619 --> 17:01.554
>> THANK YOU.

17:04.757 --> 17:06.759
>> OOH.

17:09.462 --> 17:11.397
[ CAMERA CLICKING ]

17:12.499 --> 17:14.867
[ MUSIC ]

17:16.303 --> 17:18.971
[ FROGS CROAKING ]

17:30.750 --> 17:31.351
>> OVER HERE.

17:31.351 --> 17:33.620
I THINK I FOUND IT.

17:42.129 --> 17:43.630
>> YUP, THIS IS IT.

17:43.630 --> 17:45.432
HARPER LAKE.

17:45.432 --> 17:47.600
>> OKAY, SO I THINK THE TENT

17:47.600 --> 17:50.170
SHOULD GO HERE, AND FIRE HERE.

17:52.705 --> 17:55.142
>> I'VE GOT A BETTER IDEA.

18:02.849 --> 18:05.452
LAST ONE IN'S A SQUARE!

18:07.487 --> 18:10.022
[ SPLASHING AND GIGGLING ]

18:12.292 --> 18:13.460
>> NOT... NOT YOU?

18:13.460 --> 18:14.060
[ CHUCKLING ]

18:14.060 --> 18:15.195
>> NO.

18:15.195 --> 18:16.028
THEY'RE GONNA BE DRINKING AND

18:16.028 --> 18:18.231
SMOKING, AND THE TENT WON'T BE

18:18.231 --> 18:18.965
PUT UP, AND THE FIRE

18:18.965 --> 18:20.667
WON'T BE BUILT.

18:20.667 --> 18:22.034
>> I'LL HELP.

18:22.034 --> 18:23.303
>> NO, IT'S FINE.

18:23.303 --> 18:25.772
GO HAVE FUN.

18:25.772 --> 18:29.075
>> I CAN'T SWIM.

18:29.075 --> 18:30.943
>> OKAY, COME ON.

18:45.057 --> 18:48.595
[ DISTANT COYOTE HOWLING ]

18:48.595 --> 18:49.262
>> YOU'RE NOT STILL WORRIED

18:49.262 --> 18:52.699
ABOUT DOC'S STORIES, ARE YA?

18:52.699 --> 18:54.201
>> UM, NO.

18:54.201 --> 18:56.269
I MEAN, THEY'RE JUST STORIES,

18:56.269 --> 18:58.771
RIGHT?

18:58.771 --> 18:59.506
[ SIGHING ]

18:59.506 --> 19:00.039
I'M JUST WORRIED

19:00.039 --> 19:01.274
ABOUT THOSE TWO,

19:01.274 --> 19:04.211
AND MY IDIOT COUSIN JANELLE.

19:04.211 --> 19:04.711
>> I WOULDN'T WORRY,

19:04.711 --> 19:06.279
THEY'RE WITH GEORGE.

19:06.279 --> 19:06.713
>> THAT'S WHAT

19:06.713 --> 19:08.815
I'M WORRIED ABOUT.

19:08.815 --> 19:10.217
[ CHUCKLING ]

19:10.217 --> 19:11.318
>> YOU KNOW,

19:11.318 --> 19:12.419
YOU'RE A LOT MORE FUN

19:12.419 --> 19:14.287
THAN SHE SAID YOU'D BE.

19:14.287 --> 19:16.289
>> WHO?

19:16.289 --> 19:17.056
>> JANELLE.

19:17.056 --> 19:20.026
SHE SAID YOU CAN BE KIND OF A...

19:20.026 --> 19:20.860
A PRUDE.

19:20.860 --> 19:22.128
>> WHAT?

19:22.128 --> 19:23.330
[ LOUD YELLING ]

19:23.330 --> 19:25.598
[ LAUGHTER ]

19:25.598 --> 19:26.333
>> OH, YOU SHOULD HAVE

19:26.333 --> 19:27.400
SEEN YOUR FACES.

19:27.400 --> 19:28.601
OH MY GOD.

19:28.601 --> 19:30.270
>> THAT'S NOT FUNNY.

19:30.270 --> 19:31.238
>> YEAH, IT IS.

19:31.238 --> 19:32.539
[ CHUCKLING ]

19:32.539 --> 19:34.073
>> CHECK OUT WHAT WE FOUND.

19:34.073 --> 19:35.908
[ MUSIC ]

19:35.908 --> 19:37.244
>> WHERE'D YOU FIND THAT?

19:37.244 --> 19:38.411
>> UH, I FOUND IT ON A SCARECROW

19:38.411 --> 19:39.946
IN THE FIELD BACK THERE.

19:39.946 --> 19:41.581
>> BY THE CEMETERY?

19:41.581 --> 19:43.483
>> YEAH, WHY?

19:43.483 --> 19:46.386
>> YOU HEARD THE STORIES.

19:46.386 --> 19:46.953
>> WHA-- WHAT DID YOU

19:46.953 --> 19:47.954
DO THAT FOR?

19:47.954 --> 19:49.021
>> SHE'S WORRIED ABOUT WHAT THAT

19:49.021 --> 19:51.891
OLD MAN SAID, ABOUT SCARECROW

19:51.891 --> 19:54.261
OF THE LAKE, OR SOME DUMB SHIT.

19:54.261 --> 19:55.928
YOU ARE SO NAIVE.

19:55.928 --> 19:56.996
THOSE STORIES WERE JUST MADE UP

19:56.996 --> 19:57.630
TO KEEP US FROM

19:57.630 --> 20:00.900
HAVING A GOOD TIME.

20:00.900 --> 20:02.335
>> WELL?

20:02.335 --> 20:03.770
>> DON'T WORRY, DEAR.

20:03.770 --> 20:05.472
IN ALL THE MONSTER STORIES,

20:05.472 --> 20:06.539
IT'S ALWAYS THE VIRGIN

20:06.539 --> 20:08.375
THAT GETS TO BE THE HERO.

20:08.375 --> 20:10.477
YOU CAN SAVE US ALL.

20:10.477 --> 20:11.344
>> FUCK YOU.

20:11.344 --> 20:13.513
[ CHUCKLING ]

20:14.881 --> 20:16.349
>> JUST LET HER GO.

20:16.349 --> 20:18.150
SHE CAN COOL OFF.

20:18.150 --> 20:20.487
>> BESIDES, I BROUGHT THIS.

20:20.487 --> 20:23.189
HEYYYY.

20:23.189 --> 20:25.858
>> NOW WE HAVE A CHANCE TO CHAT.

20:29.662 --> 20:33.466
[ THUDDING FOOTSTEPS ]

20:35.134 --> 20:49.449
[ MUSIC ]

21:00.393 --> 21:02.429
[ BONG BUBBLING ]

21:06.366 --> 21:08.134
>> I'M GOIN' AFTER HER.

21:08.134 --> 21:09.235
>> UGH, IT'S NOT LIKE

21:09.235 --> 21:11.338
YOU'RE GONNA GET ANY!

21:11.338 --> 21:13.706
AT LEAST FROM HER, ANYWAY.

21:16.343 --> 21:17.344
>> COOL IT, BITCH.

21:17.344 --> 21:19.712
I SAID HE'S OFF LIMITS.

21:19.712 --> 21:21.881
>> YEAH, BUT...

21:25.352 --> 21:26.252
>> MAYBE WE CAN HAVE SOME FUN

21:26.252 --> 21:27.920
WITH CLAIRE LATER?

21:27.920 --> 21:29.456
>> THAT SOUNDS PEACHY.

21:29.456 --> 21:29.989
I'D RATHER HAVE SOME FUN

21:29.989 --> 21:32.024
RIGHT NOW.

21:35.728 --> 21:37.464
[ BONG BUBBLING ]

21:37.464 --> 21:38.431
>> COME ON.

21:38.431 --> 21:40.567
>> ALL RIGHT.

21:43.135 --> 21:44.404
>> I SAID LATER.

21:44.404 --> 21:46.373
MAYBE.

21:46.373 --> 21:48.107
>> THERE YOU GO.

21:48.107 --> 21:49.942
BYE.

21:51.944 --> 21:56.182
>> HE'S OFF LIMITS...

21:56.182 --> 21:59.085
SHE'S MY COUSIN...

21:59.085 --> 22:01.688
I SAID, LATER...

22:01.688 --> 22:03.623
MAYBE...

22:03.623 --> 22:06.693
YOU LEAVE ME ALL ALONE OUT HERE?

22:06.693 --> 22:08.160
FUCKIN' BITCH!

22:08.160 --> 22:09.696
FUCKIN' HOPE THE FUCKIN'

22:09.696 --> 22:11.998
SCARECROW GETS YOU.

22:11.998 --> 22:17.404
[ MUSIC ]

22:17.404 --> 22:19.672
FUCKIN' BITCH.

22:24.143 --> 22:25.412
[ GASPING ]

22:25.412 --> 22:26.879
[ SNARLING ]

22:26.879 --> 22:29.281
[ GAGGING ]

22:40.192 --> 22:41.694
>> SMOOTH.

22:41.694 --> 22:43.430
I'M SO GONNA GET LOST.

22:43.430 --> 22:45.097
WITHOUT A FRICKIN' FLASHLIGHT,

22:45.097 --> 22:47.099
WHAT THE HELL WAS I THINKING?

23:03.282 --> 23:05.051
>> ONE-PUMP CHUMP.

23:05.051 --> 23:06.853
HOW FUCKING ANNOYING.

23:06.853 --> 23:07.887
I CHANGED MY MIND, CLAIRE,

23:07.887 --> 23:09.589
YOU CAN HAVE...

23:09.589 --> 23:10.457
>> HEY, COME BACK, COME BACK,

23:10.457 --> 23:11.491
I NEED TO TRY AGAIN.

23:11.491 --> 23:12.358
GIVE ME ANOTHER CHANCE!

23:12.358 --> 23:14.093
GIVE--

23:14.093 --> 23:16.929
[ GROWLING ]

23:16.929 --> 23:18.264
[ GRUNTING ]

23:18.264 --> 23:20.232
[ SNARLING ]

23:20.232 --> 23:22.635
[ GROANING ]

23:24.370 --> 23:26.806
[ SKULL CRUNCHING ]

23:28.841 --> 23:30.943
>> JO!

23:30.943 --> 23:34.046
JOSEPHINE, RUN!

23:34.046 --> 23:35.848
[ SCREAMING ]

23:48.260 --> 23:50.096
[ STICKS CRACKING ]

24:02.509 --> 24:04.944
>> OH, SHIT!

24:16.188 --> 24:19.325
[ SIGHING ]

24:19.325 --> 24:22.529
IT'S JUST A SCARECROW.

24:22.529 --> 24:26.432
WHAT THE FUCK?

24:26.432 --> 24:28.434
[ SNARLING ]

24:28.535 --> 24:29.769
>> AND...

24:29.769 --> 24:32.071
AS RALPH DROPPED HIS LIGHTER,

24:32.071 --> 24:33.640
THE CREATURE DEVOURED HIM...

24:33.640 --> 24:35.642
SWALLOWED HIS SOUL...

24:35.642 --> 24:37.844
DAMNING HIM FOR ALL ETERNITY.

24:37.877 --> 24:39.546
>> WAIT, WAIT, SO WAS THERE

24:39.546 --> 24:40.880
MORE THAN ONE SCARECROW?

24:40.880 --> 24:41.981
OR HOW DID IT GET FROM

24:41.981 --> 24:44.817
CAMP TO RALPH SO FAST?

24:44.817 --> 24:46.285
>> WHO'S TELLIN' THE STORY HERE?

24:46.285 --> 24:47.554
>> JESUS, TRAV,

24:47.554 --> 24:48.855
IT'S JUST A STORY.

24:48.855 --> 24:50.222
AM I RIGHT, BEC?

24:50.222 --> 24:51.290
>> HMM?

24:51.290 --> 24:52.258
>> GOD, STOP FLIRTING

24:52.258 --> 24:54.060
WITH EVERY MALE YOU SEE.

24:54.060 --> 24:55.461
>> I WASN'T FLIRTING WITH YOU.

24:55.461 --> 24:56.996
>> OOH, BURN!

24:56.996 --> 24:58.064
>> COME ON, YOU TWO, LOCK IT UP.

24:58.064 --> 24:59.398
I WANNA HEAR THE REST OF THIS.

24:59.398 --> 25:00.266
>> NO, COME ON, TRAVIS,

25:00.266 --> 25:01.734
I'VE HEARD ENOUGH.

25:01.734 --> 25:05.037
>> AW, YOU SCARED?

25:05.037 --> 25:06.338
>> HOLD UP.

25:06.338 --> 25:08.641
IT'S JUST AN URBAN LEGEND,

25:08.641 --> 25:09.408
RIGHT?

25:09.408 --> 25:10.476
>> WELL, THERE IS TRUTH TO ALL

25:10.476 --> 25:12.278
URBAN LEGENDS, ISN'T THERE?

25:12.278 --> 25:13.613
>> SO WHAT HAPPENED?

25:13.613 --> 25:14.380
>> COME ON, IT KILLED THEM ALL,

25:14.380 --> 25:15.314
RIGHT?

25:15.314 --> 25:16.315
>> BECAUSE THEY SKINNY DIPPED

25:16.315 --> 25:17.383
AND HAD SEX?

25:17.383 --> 25:20.086
>> AND GOT DRUNK, AND HIGH.

25:20.086 --> 25:20.820
>> AND LET'S NOT FORGET,

25:20.820 --> 25:22.221
SOMEBODY DEFILED THE SCARECROW.

25:22.221 --> 25:23.289
>> AND IT GOT THEM ALL.

25:23.289 --> 25:24.724
>> EXCEPT...

25:24.724 --> 25:25.958
THE VIRGIN.

25:25.958 --> 25:26.325
[all together]

25:26.325 --> 25:27.927
>> EXCEPT THE VIRGIN.

25:27.927 --> 25:28.628
>> WELL, I GUESS I DON'T HAVE TO

25:28.628 --> 25:29.596
TELL THE REST OF THE STORY,

25:29.596 --> 25:30.062
SINCE YOU ALL HAVE IT

25:30.062 --> 25:31.030
FIGURED OUT.

25:31.030 --> 25:32.865
>> WAIT, SO...

25:32.865 --> 25:34.166
WAS ALL THIS UP AT THE LAKE,

25:34.166 --> 25:35.668
BY THE HILLS?

25:35.668 --> 25:37.870
>> AYE, T'WAS, T'WAS.

25:37.870 --> 25:40.006
LET ALL WARY TRAVELERS BEWARE,

25:40.006 --> 25:41.941
SPOIL NOT NATURE.

25:41.941 --> 25:42.675
>> HEY, WE ARE

25:42.675 --> 25:43.776
ONLY GOING CAMPING.

25:43.776 --> 25:44.243
>> YEAH, YOU'RE KINDA

25:44.243 --> 25:45.712
HARSHING OUR BUZZES.

25:45.712 --> 25:46.312
>> YOU CITY FOLK

25:46.312 --> 25:48.014
ARE ALL THE SAME,

25:48.014 --> 25:49.248
TRAIPSIN' THROUGH NATURE

25:49.248 --> 25:49.749
AND GOIN' WHERE

25:49.749 --> 25:51.217
YOU AREN'T WANTED.

25:51.217 --> 25:52.184
YOU NEED TO LEARN TO RESPECT

25:52.184 --> 25:54.954
WHAT ISN'T YOURS.

25:54.954 --> 25:56.155
STRANGE AND DARK THINGS

25:56.155 --> 25:58.357
LURK IN THE NIGHT...

25:58.357 --> 26:00.192
AND IN THOSE WOODS.

26:00.192 --> 26:02.161
YOU'D BEST BE CAREFUL.

26:02.161 --> 26:03.830
[ CLATTERING ]

26:03.830 --> 26:04.697
DAMN IT, DOC!

26:04.697 --> 26:05.798
STOP MAKIN' A MESS!

26:05.798 --> 26:06.633
>> SORRY, JO.

26:06.633 --> 26:07.299
I GOT ALL CAUGHT UP

26:07.299 --> 26:08.701
IN YOUR STORY.

26:08.701 --> 26:10.637
>> THIS ISN'T FUNNY, GUYS.

26:10.637 --> 26:11.170
>> OH, SHE'S JUST

26:11.170 --> 26:12.939
TRYING TO SCARE US.

26:12.939 --> 26:13.840
WE WOULD HAVE HEARD ABOUT THIS.

26:13.840 --> 26:14.373
I MEAN, WHY WASN'T IT

26:14.373 --> 26:14.941
ON THE NEWS?

26:14.941 --> 26:15.441
>> WAIT A MINUTE,

26:15.441 --> 26:16.408
HOLD THE GODDAMN PHONE.

